The paper discusses the security challenges of real-time Internet of Things (RT-IoT) systems, which involves both cyber-physical systems and networked embedded devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the real-time requirements of RT-IoT systems, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.ET (Embedded Systems and Cyber-Physical Systems). Additionally, the paper discusses the connectivity aspect of RT-IoT systems, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions the need for secure frameworks, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.CR, cs.ET, and cs.SY (Systems and Control), with cs.NI and cs.SE being less likely but still possible.
